Set.name: Reaction
Set.concept: The REACT set reports an overt discernible reaction by the submarine contact to either a ship pass or aircraft fly-by. The REACT set must be followed by a TMPOS set reporting the loss of visual contact or the last pass by a ship or aircraft. After an initial reaction is reported, a separate REACT set must be used for each subsequent approach by the aircraft or ship to the contact, regardless of whether a reaction occurred on each pass.
Set.description: The REACT set is used to report an overt discernible reaction by the contact to either a ship pass or aircraft fly-by.
